cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with medical image annotation using active learning and U-shape network, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new criterion to evaluate the efforts of doctors annotating medical images, which involves quantitative calculations and optimization, indicating a focus on AI and optimization techniques, respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of medical informatics, suggesting cs.MED (Medical Informatics) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves optimization of annotation efforts, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
